v70 one male goat for a sin offering;
v71 and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old. This was the offering of Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.
v72 On the eleventh day Pagiel the son of Ochran, prince of the children of Asher,
v73 gave his offering: one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a meal offering;
v74 one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense;
